            <p><strong>Discoverer:</strong> Max Wertheimer & Kurt Koffka (1912)</p>
            <p>Max Wertheimer and Kurt Koffka were investigating how the human brain perceives whole objects rather than a collection of separate pixels. They created this split ring to show that object continuity (wholeness) directly influences how we perceive basic attributes like brightness.</p>
          </div>
